{"body": "I agree there are workarounds. \n\nBut I still contend it is a bug that the #tag method, that takes attribute values as input, can allow that input to spill over out of the delimited attribute it is generating. If it isn't worth the perf hit to do the string substitution, maybe it should fail fast and raise if the attribute value contains a double quote character, after passing through ERB::Util.h.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8512828", "created_at": "2012-09-12T22:47:06Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7611#issuecomment-8512828", "updated_at": "2012-09-12T22:52:29Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7611, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joshuaflanagan/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joshuaflanagan/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joshuaflanagan/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/joshuaflanagan", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joshuaflanagan/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/joshuaflanagan", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joshuaflanagan/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/10adb7caa4eff9c02d244172bc8db6df?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F3592eda3e878dde5bc1bddde6ffabe36.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joshuaflanagan/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joshuaflanagan/received_events", "gravatar_id": "10adb7caa4eff9c02d244172bc8db6df", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joshuaflanagan/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "joshuaflanagan", "type": "User", "id": 81455, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joshuaflanagan/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523ddb11bd354364b900abcd"}, "id": 8512828, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7611"}
